data.chText: （尤指建筑物的）外部，外观，表面，外貌
data.enText: the outside of sth, especially a building
The exterior of the house needs painting.
the way that sb appears or behaves, especially when this is very different from their real feelings or character

data.chText: 他表面上自信，内心极度紧张。
data.enText: Beneath his confident exterior, he was desperately nervous.
on the outside of sth; done or happening outdoors

data.chText: 外景是在沼泽地拍摄的。
data.enText: The filming of the exterior scenes was done on the moors.

simple_means.memory_skill: exter 外 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 外部的

tr: the outer side or surface of something
the region that is outside of something
situated in or suitable for the outdoors or outside of a building

value.def: The exterior of something is its outside surface.

example.ex: In one ad the viewer scarcely sees the car's exterior...
example.tran: 在一则广告中，观众几乎看不到汽车的外观。

example.ex: The exterior of the building was elegant and graceful.
example.tran: 这座大厦外观雅致而优美。

value.def: You can refer to someone's usual appearance or behaviour as their exterior, especially when it is very different from their real character.

example.ex: According to Mandy, Pat's tough exterior hides a shy and sensitive soul.
example.tran: 据曼迪说，帕特彪悍的外表下隐藏着一颗害羞且敏感的心。

gramarinfo.label: usu sing, usu with supp, oft poss N

value.tran: （尤指与实际性格相差甚远的）外表，外貌，外在

value.def: You use exterior to refer to the outside parts of something or things that are outside something.

example.ex: The exterior walls were made of pre-formed concrete.
example.tran: 外墙用的是预制混凝土。

trans: 外定向；外方位；外方位模式

partsOfSpeech.dec: anter〔= ante前面〕+ ior 较…的，属于…的 → 较早的
exter 外 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 外部的
infer 下面 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 低下的，下等的
inter 内 + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 内部的
post 后 + er + ior 较…的，属于…的 → 较后的
sen 年老 + ior 人 → 年长者
super 上 + ior 人 → 上级
warr〔= war战争〕+ ior 人 → 勇士，斗士
